snippet.textDisplay: Hi colleen. I know you aren't going to see this but I just wanted to say I've been watching your videos since the ninth grade (I'm 20 now) and I hope this doesn't sound cheesy but you're like the big sister I never had. You're such a kind person with a gorgeous family filled with such sincere people and you guys give me a lot of hope. As someone that has been through and is still experiencing depression and anxiety (I started watching your videos around the time I began experiencing the symptoms even though I didn't know I had it yet) I can honestly say your presence on the platform has brought me so much comfort. Thank you for being a light on YouTube and for remaining so kind and humble. You are so hard working it inspires me to be better and try to focus on being healthier so I can pursue what I want just like you do. I know people say nice things to you all the time but I hope you see what a gift you are in so many people's lives. You make me feel like I'm not alone. I hope you have the most merry christmas. ❤

snippet.textDisplay:
SANTA WARNING NEXT TIME!! It is now 4:42 am I started this video at 6 pm, Santa meltdown mode just ended...
.
.
There are moms like me out there that have little kiddo ears running around, minding their own buisness, drawing on the wall or something, all the while we are sitting on the couch after a long day standing in line for almost 4 hours, with a screeching hoard of children(and nagging husbands), asking their moms how much longer till we see Santa. Just to get to the front of the line and "Santa" had to go to the little elves room making everyone in line behind us cry and groan at the prospect of any additional hour or more of just standing in line that may be added to their day. Twenty five minutes pass (the line is thinning, not that it matters now) the kids no longer want to see Santa; it took too long. Now everyone is probably hungry and upset they've missed their nap. Unhappy with the Christmas Card stuck on the fridge with a magnetic letter 'p', that over priced photo of screaming children on Santas lap, all for what? Children now happy and forgetting all about the traumatic experience of the day come in to hear us watching your videos. We ignore this as we usually do until we hear you say the forbidden words and the panic sets in hoping they didn't hear and the fear of the inevitable major meltdown begins, years too early. The game just starting. It's been 11 hours of screaming and crying over santa only to be triggered by an older sibling going and reminding them why they are upset, starting the whole thing over again.
